	abstract = {Artificial Intelligence (AI) has rapidly transformed the fields of policing, intelligence, and counterterrorism. Agencies around the world are increasingly adopting advanced technologies to enhance their capabilities, improve efficiency, and respond more effectively to threats. These emerging technologies provide opportunities that were previously unattainable, enabling predictive analysis, real-time surveillance, and faster decision-making processes. However, the widespread use of AI and other advanced tools also introduces unique challenges and risks. These include potential misuse, ethical dilemmas, data privacy concerns, and vulnerabilities to adversarial attacks, all of which require careful strategic planning and robust regulatory frameworks to manage effectively. Applications and Strategic Implementation of AI in Policing offers a comprehensive exploration of how AI is transforming the fields of policing, intelligence, and counterterrorism. It examines both the opportunities and threats posed by AI, offering a unique, practitioner-oriented framework for integrating AI into law enforcement. Covering topics such as AI-powered ransomware, 3D crime scene reconstruction, and deepfake video detection, this book is a critical academic resource for graduate and doctoral students, law enforcement leaders, intelligence professionals, researchers, policymakers, and more. © 2026 by IGI Global Scientific Publishing. All rights reserved.},
