	affiliations = {University of Virginia, United States},
	abstract = {Artificial intelligence (AI) can transform public procurement processes and improve public service delivery. This review provides an overview of AI's impact on procurement structures. The analysis identifies four primary drivers enhancing service delivery. Predictive analytics enable procurement officers to make informed decisions by identifying patterns and trends. Rational contracting systems ensure contract compliance, guaranteeing high-quality goods and services while optimizing public funds. Technology like blockchain can improve transparency and accountability by creating immutable records of procurement activities. Finally, digital marketplaces can connect buyers and suppliers through online platforms, increasing competition and enabling access to suppliers and products. Subsequent discussion focuses on four schools of thought concerning AI's influence on public service delivery: efficiency-orientation, accountability and transparency, equity and fairness, and innovation and citizen-centricity. While digital innovations drive development, exercising caution and developing mechanisms to safeguard citizen trust in public service delivery without stifling innovation is essential. © 2024 Edward Elgar Publishing.},
